ASX-listed lithium-focused exploration company Force Commodities is aggressively advancing two lithium projects in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) – with its efforts currently concentrated on advancing its 70%-owned Kitotolo lithium project, and its 51%-owned Kanuka lithium production project, MD Jason Brewer tells Chantelle Kotze during the recent DRC Mining Week conference and exhibition. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 8 2018. It will be published online on the 20th September 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy